The Voice of Conscience

The unbearable weight
Jehad Alshrafi
(Photographer)
TOI take:
Published on: Jun 20, 2025
A grieving Palestinian father holds the body of his child, killed in an Israeli airstrike on Gaza, a moment captured at Al-Shifa Hospital. Images like this lay bare the staggering human toll of the conflict. Over 3,300 people have died in Gaza, with more than 13,000 wounded. Among the dead are at least 700 children.
The briefcase
2025
James Colomina
(Photographer)
TOI take:
Published on: May 22, 2025
French street artist James Colomina’s installation The Briefcase is displayed on the pavement at Tokyo’s Shibuya Crossing. The piece depicts a 'salaryman' consumed by routine and stripped of identity in the pressures of daily corporate life. It features a red briefcase, symbolizing work and conformity, with arms, legs and a tie poking out of it.
The tongue-out genius
1951
Arthur Sasse
(Photographer)
TOI take:
Published on: May 14, 2025
Arthur Sasse’s 1951 picture of Albert Einstein playfully sticking out his tongue on his 72nd birthday captured the physicist’s light, nutty professor side, challenging the world’s perception of him as merely a serious genius, a portrayal he clearly enjoyed, as he ordered nine copies. This later became the most expensive Einstein portrait ever sold.
